On Saturday, 22 May 2021, government will hand over land and title deeds to farmers at Tafelkop in the Groblersdal, Sekhukhune District of Limpopo Province. President Cyril Ramaphosa will  lead the handover ceremony supported by Ministers of  Public Works and Infrastructure; Agriculture, Land Reform and Rural Development; Justice and Correctional Services as well as Acting Minister in The Presidency responsible for Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation. The handover ceremony is the culmination of a land reform process. The ceremony will see 30 black farmers being presented with title deeds. Members of the public in the area are advised that traffic flow on Route R33 will be affected. Members of the media are advised that a fair selection pool arrangement has been put in place to comply with the COVID-19 protocols. Only accredited media will be allowed to attend the event onsite. Other media are encouraged to follow the proceedings of the event via livestream on the below government social media channels:Facebook:  http://facebook.com/GovernmentZA Twitter:       http://twitter.com/GovernmentZA YouTube:   https://www.youtube.com/user/GovernmentZA Media enquiries: Zara Nicholson Media Liaison Officer to Minister of Public Works and Infrastructure: Patricia de LilleMobile: 079 416 5996Zara.Nicholson@dpw.gov.za Reggie NgcoboMedia Liaison Officer to Minister of Agriculture, Land Reform and Rural Development: Thoko DidizaMobile: 066 298b0980Mlo.minister@dalrrd.gov.za